channel.title: Port forwarding
channel.description:
I'm using PortFoward.com like it says on the tutorial and im up to this part:
We need to have the correct Name Server IP addresses. If we do not, you will not be able to browse the web. There are a couple ways to get these. The first way is to log into your router's web interface, and look at your router's status page. I need to find this for a NETGEAR DG834G, can anyone help me find it?
